ffort that goes into a product.<br/><em>—Rory Sutherland, British ad executive</em></p></blockquote><p>The chart’s importance can be appreciated if the audience perceives you have sunk a lot of resources into it. There is a bit of a paradox here: Making an irrational investment in the show is a rational way of conveying value. Every time I pursue a project scope that seems a little irrational, I am bolstered knowing that it may be the crazy effort that helps it succeed. From this vantage, chasing crazy is a worthwhile pursuit.</p><p>When it comes to rational storytelling, I believe extravagant data graphics is one of the few tools we have to inform audiences that their attention will not be wasted.</p><h2>Going Forward</h2><p>This is the last entry about the value created <em>without </em>reading data graphics. Internally, I organize these three essays with emoji:</p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F30e605e9-f749-46de-8d01-8307f4eb3205_1920x556.jpeg" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/mYXsGt_ 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5UFAExly6saH_ 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/PUhZWb6rjYr0O6vGB47AK- 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/wBAsgtYWExq_XpugeRcShXF9OST_Gfbp082_u61Lqcw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xNDU2LGNfbGltaXQsZl93ZWJwLHFfYXV0bzpnb29kLGZsX3Byb2dyZXNzaXZlOnN0ZWVwL2h0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGc3Vic3RhY2stcG9zdC1tZWRpYS5zMy5hbWF6b25hd3MuY29tJTJGcHVibGljJTJGaW1hZ2VzJTJGMzBlNjA1ZTktZjc0OS00NmRlLThkMDEtODMwN2Y0ZWIzMjA1XzE5MjB4NTU2LmpwZWc= 1456w" sizes="100vw"/><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/amT-IqpdmwgI3dQNGoLZGA-" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/SelpfqTyb5P4seouZTC-LsZlVbIB- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/onygoq3xfjvFvV0A7DRuLqZnQQjotSn9Mg-6SNmTL6A=/aHR0c